cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MM

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the constrained capacity of multiple-antenna fading coherent channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses optimization of the reliable information transmission rate, which falls under the category of cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of expansions to study the impact of various parameters on the reliable information transmission rate suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper mentions the design of power allocation and precoding schemes, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
